1 unit Lime
1 unit Bell Pepper
1 unit Mini Cucumber
¼ ounce Cilantro
4 tablespoon Guacamole
2 tablespoon Yogurt
1 teaspoon Chili Flakes
½ cup Feta Cheese
2 unit Flour Tortillas
16 ounce Refried Black Beans
Salt
Pepper

• Wash and dry produce.

• Quarter lime. Roughly chop cilantro. Halve, core, and slice bell pepper into
strips. Trim and halve cucumber lengthwise, then cut into ¼-inch planks.

• In a large bowl, combine guacamole, yogurt, juice from one lime wedge
(two wedges for 4 servings), and as much cilantro and as many chili
flakes as you like until smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

• Add bell pepper, cucumber, and feta to bowl with dressing. Toss until
fully coated.

• Wrap tortillas in damp paper towels; microwave until warm and pliable,
30 seconds.

• Lay tortillas on a clean work surface. Spread a thin layer of refried
beans on the bottom two-thirds of each tortilla. Place veggies on top of
refried beans.

• Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and
right sides toward filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to
form wraps.

• Halve wraps on a diagonal. Divide between plates and serve.